From: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 18 Oct 2021 14:10:05 -0700
Subject: ethernet: fec: use eth_hw_addr_gen()
Patch-mainline: v5.16-rc1
Git-commit: ba3fdfe32bb94d712188fbdd37d4e64edbf8e65d
References: jsc#PED-1565

Commit 406f42fa0d3c ("net-next: When a bond have a massive amount
of VLANs...") introduced a rbtree for faster Ethernet address look
up. To maintain netdev->dev_addr in this tree we need to make all
the writes to it got through appropriate helpers.

Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Vladimir Oltean <vladimir.oltean@nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c |    5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fec_main.c
@@ -1731,11 +1731,8 @@ static int fec_get_mac(struct net_device
 		return 0;
 	}
 
-	eth_hw_addr_set(ndev, iap);
-
 	/* Adjust MAC if using macaddr */
-	if (iap == macaddr)
-		 ndev->dev_addr[ETH_ALEN-1] = macaddr[ETH_ALEN-1] + fep->dev_id;
+	eth_hw_addr_gen(ndev, iap, iap == macaddr ? fep->dev_id : 0);
 
 	return 0;
 }
